This paper deals with natural language processing techniques applied to dream reports, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on word-embedding techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the use of Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA), which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.NE, in that order.
